<br>
I got my mask this evening. It took me two weeks of off-and-on camping. However this past Friday night I went down there and said to myself I wouldn't leave until I got it. The problem was that the assassin is hardly ever camped on my server (Vallon Zek). <br>
<br>
Tonight (Sunday) I managed to get lucky. I had been starting to go delerious looking at that Loch Ness monster shaped green slime on the wall near the ladder up to the SR. Or is it the stain from Gumby when he was slain by the frogs? I dunno.. I'm tired. This whole weekend I was popping in and out to see if the assassin had spawned. Good news is that I got my alternate character up three levels. Bad news is that I finally got the mask tonight, right before bed time for work tomorrow. I'll stop rambling.. I really am tired.<br>
<br>
I popped in, the assassin was up. I asked everyone I knew that had ever given me an inkling of a reason to think they'd let me loot the mask. Nada. Finally I worked out a plan to have an inkie hunting in LGuk pretend that his human rogue was camped there for the mask. That way folks might not mind if he looted it. I played my alternate while the plan was set into motion. Well I got restless after about 30 minutes (I really thought THIS assassin was the one) and logged back in as my rogue. Oof... folks upstairs in the store room?!?! I really thought I missed my chance... so hell, I said, might as well see who had beaten me to the punch (again). Behold... the assassin's corpse was sitting there with a bunch of evils meditating around it. Ninja loot-&gt; rehide-&gt; jump-&gt; BAM. I had a Mask of Deception.<br>
<br>
I must say it was definitely done in the style of a true rogue although my game etiquette was a tad unsat. Turns out they were waiting for a younger evil guildmate to make his way down and loot the mask. Sorry pal, two weeks of staring at slime on a wall will do that to a rogue.<br>
<br>
<br>
Vagan of Vallon Zek<br>
<br>
P.S. Please refer to my post in the Main Lounge section on my trouble with the Mask.<br>
